Overview This document defines the JSON structure required by the Content Package Manager. The backend expects a root object containing sap.package. Certain fields are mandatory, and validation rules apply as described below.

Top-level

sap.package (object) [REQUIRED]
sap.package fields

id (string) [REQUIRED]
packageVersion (object) [REQUIRED]
version (string) [REQUIRED]
Format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH or MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH-<timestamp>
Examples: 1.2.3, 1.2.3-1705940000000
upgradeNotification (string) [REQUIRED]
Must be one of the API-defined enum values (e.g., NONE, MAJOR, MAJOR_MINOR, MAJOR_MINOR_PATCH, ALL). Any invalid value is treated as ALL at runtime.
contents (array) [CONDITIONALLY REQUIRED]
Either contents or cdmEntities must be non-empty (at least one item).
cdmEntities (array) [CONDITIONALLY REQUIRED]
Either contents or cdmEntities must be non-empty (at least one item).
releaseNotes (any) [OPTIONAL]
prerequisites (any) [OPTIONAL]
dependencies (object) [OPTIONAL]
packages (array of string) [OPTIONAL]
consumption (any) [OPTIONAL]
contents item structure Each entry in sap.package.contents must include:

manifest (object) [REQUIRED]
sap.artifact (object) [REQUIRED]
id (string) [REQUIRED]
type (string) [REQUIRED]
Must align with the API’s ContentType enum. Note: only entries with type = CDM_BUSINESSAPP contribute destination configuration metadata.
artifactVersion (object) [REQUIRED]
version (string) [REQUIRED]
destinations (object) [OPTIONAL]
Map of destinationName -> { description?: string, scope?: string }
scope must be a valid enum value per API; invalid/missing values default to user-provided.
baseURL (string) [REQUIRED]
Either baseURL, or legacy baseUrl/baseDir is accepted.
Interpreted as a folder path (trailing “/” normalized). The system expects a data.zip file under this path.
i18n (string) [OPTIONAL]
Relative path to i18n file under the artifact (default: i18n/i18n.properties). Used to derive the base i18n path.
Validation rules and behavior

sap.package is required; missing it fails validation.
sap.package.id, sap.package.packageVersion.version, and sap.package.packageVersion.upgradeNotification are required.
Version must match regex: ^([0-9]+).([0-9]+).([0-9]+)(-([0-9]+).*)?$
At least one of contents or cdmEntities must be provided and non-empty.
Each contents item requires manifest.sap.artifact.id, type, artifactVersion.version, and a baseURL (or legacy baseUrl/baseDir).
destinations are optional. If present, entries may include description and scope. Invalid scope values default to user-provided.
Internal/system-managed fields (not required when authoring manifests): origin, status, updatedOn, newVersion, newVersionOrigin, latestReleaseNote, upgradeFailedVersion, upgradeFailedVersionOrigin, installedOn, upgradeNotificationStrategy, upgradeNotificationUserStrategy, configuration, metadataOfConfiguration.
If updatedOn is present, acceptable formats are:
ISO 8601 with milliseconds and Z suffix (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'), or
a numeric epoch millis, or
a Java Date during internal processing. Typically this is set by the system.
Notes

destinations metadata is aggregated only for contents with type CDM_BUSINESSAPP to build deploy configuration metadata.
i18n path defaults to i18n/i18n.properties under baseURL if not specified.
dependencies.packages should be an array; non-array values are ignored.